com.castlabs.sdk.subtitles

Class SubtitlesPlugin.SubtitlesPluginComponent

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.castlabs.sdk.subtitles.SubtitlesPlugin.SubtitlesPluginComponent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PlayerControllerPlugin.Component, SubtitlesPlugin.SubtitleViewListener
    Enclosing class:
    SubtitlesPlugin

    public static class SubtitlesPlugin.SubtitlesPluginComponent
extends java.lang.Object
implements PlayerControllerPlugin.Component, SubtitlesPlugin.SubtitleViewListener
    Exposes the underlying SubtitlesView. In order to get such instance, you should set a listener which will be called back when the SubtitlesView is ready.
    Since:
    4.2.0

      • setSubtitleViewListener

        public void setSubtitleViewListener(@Nullable
                                    SubtitlesPlugin.SubtitleViewListener subtitleViewListener)
        Sets a SubtitleViewListener that will be invoked whenever the underlying SubtitlesView is ready. In case the SubtitleView had already been created, this method will immediately call SubtitlesPlugin.SubtitleViewListener.onSubtitleViewReady(SubtitlesView, boolean) with such SubtitleView.
        Parameters:
        subtitleViewListener - the listener to set

      • onSubtitleViewReady

        Specified by:
        onSubtitleViewReady in interface SubtitlesPlugin.SubtitleViewListener
        Parameters:
        view - the SubtitlesView where subtitles will be rendered.
        created - whether the view has been created by the Plugin or already existed, for instance in a SubtitlesViewComponent.
